 B (§§ 5201–5212) of title V of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/297"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–297","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-04-28"},"text":"Apr. 28, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/385"},"text":"102 Stat. 385","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 27 (§ 2501 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s2501"},"text":"section 2501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id626d9f58-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/437/s409"},"text":"Section 409 of Pub. L. 94–437","children":[],"tail":" is based on section 157 of title I of S. 1790, One Hundred Eleventh Congress, as reported by the Committee on Indian Affairs of the Senate in Dec. 2009, which was enacted into law by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/148/s10221/a"},"text":"section 10221(a) of Pub. L. 111–148","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id626d9f59-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2020—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–260","children":[],"tail":" substituted “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5301"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 5301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) or the Tribally Controlled Schools Act of 1988 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s2501"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 2501","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)” for “("},{"tag":"ref","